          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and shape",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub {{unsalted-butter}} into {{self-raising-flour}} until the mixture resembles breadcrumbs. Stir in {{caster-sugar}}, {{mixed-spice}}, {{currants}}, {{mixed-peel}}, and {{lemon}} zest. Add the beaten {{eggs}} and {{double-cream}} and mix to a firm dough. Divide into 8 portions. Shape each into a thick, slightly flattened round about 7 cm across. Place on lined baking trays and press in the cherry and almond decoration if using. Chill for 30 minutes. Heat the oven to 190°C (170°C fan).",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 18 to 20 minutes until golden and set. The rascals should be firm when pressed gently at the edge. Cool on a wire rack for 10 minutes before eating.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
